Solution: Riddle Registry (picoCTF)
I solved the "Riddle Registry" lab on picoCTF by analyzing the provided file named "Hidden Confidential Document". Below is the step-by-step walkthrough of the solution:

1. Metadata Analysis
I used ExifTool to inspect the metadata of the document. ExifTool is a powerful utility used to read, write, and edit meta information in various file types.

2. Finding the Hidden Credential
While examining the tags, I noticed a Base64-encoded string within the Author field.

3. Decoding the Password
To retrieve the plain text, I decoded the string using the following command in the terminal:

echo -n "encoded_text" | base64 -d
Breakdown of the command:
echo -n: The -n (no newline) flag ensures that no hidden newline character is added to the string, sending only the exact text within the quotes to the next command.
base64 -d: The -d (decode) flag takes the encoded string and converts it back into a human-readable format.
The resulting output revealed the cleartext password required to complete the challenge.

